{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ZStack"]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ZStack\/geometryGroup()"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from its parent view.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"title":"geometryGroup()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}],"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore6ZStackV","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"10.15","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"tvOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"visionOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false},{"name":"watchOS","unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"6.0","beta":false,"deprecated":false}],"symbolKind":"method","remoteSource":{"fileName":"RendererEffect.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L294"}},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/zstack\/geometrygroup()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed down to each subview.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may be added and removed at different times the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ZStack/geometryGroup()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ZStack\/geometryGroup()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/zstack\/geometrygroup()","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/ZStack":{"title":"ZStack","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/zstack","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ZStack","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ZStack","abstract":[{"text":"A view that overlays its subviews, aligning them in both axes.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ZStack","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"title":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","abstract":[{"text":"A type that represents part of your appâ€™s user interface and provides","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"modifiers that you use to configure views.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","title":"OpenSwiftUI","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}]}}}